text: Ectoedemia aegaeica is a moth of the family Nepticulidae. It is endemic to mainland Greece and Rhodes. The larvae feed on Vitex agnus-castus. They mine the leaves of their host plant. The mine strongly resembles that of Ectoedeia groschkei, but is somewhat smaller. ==External links== *bladmineerders.nl *Fauna Europaea Category:Nepticulidae Category:Moths of Europe
title: Ectoedemia aegaeica
